    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="702"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/475</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 29, 6.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1025. Department’s 848, January 26, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d702fn1">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <persName>Belmont</persName> replies as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In very general way tonnage question has been discussed here and should
                            be taken up later by competent representatives [familiar with?]
                            practices now in force in the United States. Certain facilities apart
                            from agreement now under consideration are likely to be secured at a
                            northern port, but in meantime whatever use you have made of bunker
                            licenses to influence routing and obtaining tonnage should be used
                            discreetly as suggested in Embassy’s 1007, January 20, 6 p.m. [<hi
                                rend="italic">21, 10 a.m.</hi>]<note n="1" xml:id="d702fn2">Not
                                printed.</note> Had no intention of conveying advice to make
                            sweeping use of bunker coaling as pressure. This would irritate and
                            embarrass situation. Advantageous moment in view of sinkings of Spanish
                            ships to get into closer relations. <persName>Belmont</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
